FBIS3-8745 "dreeu050_d_94013" FBIS-EEU-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 SLOVAKIA Industrial Production Down 1.2 Percent in Jan LD1403181894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1100 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403181894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1100 GMT 14 Mar 94 Language: Slovak Article Type:BFN [Summary] Rudolf Krc, chairman of the Statistical Office of the Slovak Republic, briefed the media today about the development of the Slovak economy in January 1994. For example, the consumption of the population, assessed on the basis of retail trade takings, was just below 16 billion korunas. Compared to December 1993, this is a drop of 21 percent. Krc said that, compared to December 1993, industrial production dropped by 1.2 percent in January.
